article.headline: Creighton 78, Florida A&amp,M 53
article.story: OMAHA, Neb. -- Darryl Ashford had 17 points and three other Creighton players scored in double figures in a 78-53 victory against Florida A&M on Tuesday night. The Bluejays (1-1) made 11 3-point shots en route to winning their 15th straight home opener. Ethan Wragge had 16 points off the bench for Creighton. Kenny Lawson Jr. added 11 points and Cavel Witter 10. Florida A&M (0-2) got 13 points from Rasheem Jenkins, while Dale Hughes and Brandon Bryant had 10 points each. The Rattlers finished with 29 turnovers while shooting just 32.1 percent from the floor. Creighton had a 46-26 halftime cushion and led by as many as 32 points in the second half.
